          <td bgcolor="" valign="top"><!-- #BeginEditable "Body" --> 
            <table width=100% border=0 cellpadding=0 cellspacing=0>
<tr><td width=1><img src="/lotr/gfx/mom/blu_01.gif" width=6 height=6></td><td width=100% background="/lotr/gfx/mom/blu_02.gif"></td>
<td width=1><img src="/lotr/gfx/mom/blu_03.gif" width=6 height=6></td></tr>
<tr><td background="/lotr/gfx/mom/blu_04.gif"><img src="/lotr/gfx/mom/clear.gif" height=35 width=1></td>
<td background="/lotr/gfx/mom/blu_05.gif" class="headerbg"><font class="h1font"><font color="#FFFFFF"><table cellspacing=0 cellpadding=0 border=0 width=100%><TR><td><font class="h1font">Tournament Reports</td><form method='post' action=''><td align='right' valign='bottom'><select name='select' onChange='go(this)'><option selected>More DeckTech Tournament Reports</option><option value='#'> </option><option value='/swccg/treports/index.php3'>Star Wars: CCG</option><option value='/lotr/treports/treports.php'>Lord of the Rings</option><option value='/magination/treports/treports.php'>Magi-Nation Duel</option><option value='/swtcg/treports/treports.php'>Star Wars TCG</option></select></td></form></tr></table></font></B></td><td background="/lotr/gfx/mom/blu_06.gif"></td></tr>
	<tr><td background="/lotr/gfx/mom/whi_07.gif"></td>
		<td bgcolor="#FFFFFF" background="/lotr/gfx/mom/whi_08.gif"><font class="bfont"><font class="h1font"> Superbowl Action, CA 2/3/02<br></font><br><font class="h2font"> <b>Overall Rating:</b> </font><img src="/lotr/gfx/star2.gif" width="19" height="21" border="0" align="absmiddle"><img src="/lotr/gfx/star2.gif" width="19" height="21" border="0" align="absmiddle"><img src="/lotr/gfx/star2.gif" width="19" height="21" border="0" align="absmiddle"><img src="/lotr/gfx/star2.gif" width="19" height="21" border="0" align="absmiddle"><img src="/lotr/gfx/star2.gif" width="19" height="21" border="0" align="absmiddle"><font size='1'>(5.00)</font><br><font class="h2font"> <b>Author:</b> <A HREF='http://www.decktech.net/lotr/main/mpage.php?member=5711'>Michael "Longshot" Mendoza</A></font><font class="afont"> <a href='http://www.decktech.net/lotr/main/mpage.php?member=5711&sub=1'> (Subscribe to this member)</a><br><font class="h2font"> <b>Date Submitted:</b> February 3, 2002</font><p align='justify'><blockquote><font class="bfont"> So its Superbowl weekend....eh, so what.  That&#39;s what I was saying to myself anyway.  Sure, I love football, but when Pittsburgh lost I threw in the towel for this season.  So I decide to go to a LOTR tourney in Castro Valley (in the east bay of the SF bay area).  One of my local players in Berkeley, Ray Liu, was going there, so I head from SF to Berkeley and meet him there.  <br>
<br>
I&#39;m fixing my deck on the way, trying to decide what to play (I had changed my deck for a multiplayer tourney before today).  So I make it pretty much the same as my last 1 vs 1 tourney, an archery deck using Gandalf, Arwen, Lego, Aragorn, Boromir, Sam, Frodo, (all rare versions except Sam) using bows and Strength of Spirits to do directed archery.  Shadow was Nazgul with anti-archer stuff like All Blades Perish & Relentless Charges.  I start rare Gandalf, Rare Frodo, Rare Ring, and Green Dragon Inn to pull Sam (I normally bid 3 or 4).  We have 12 players when Ron Berg (the TD and local Decipher PC) shows up and we start this 5 game tourney.  I&#39;d never been here before, so all but 2 players here were people I never played.<br>
<br>
Game 1 v Jason&#39;s Hobbits (R-frodo and the 3 C-hobbits)<br>
He bids 6 to let me go first.  I pull Sam, he pulls off my burdens.  Jason&#39;s playing Uruks for shadow, he plays nothing at site 2 so I move on to 3, where he plays an Uruk which wounds Gandalf.  His turn, he starts playing Hobbits like mad, Party Guests and Farmers (to get his site 1 out, the site making hobbits cost -1).  But no Gaffer, Rosie, Farmer Maggot, or Bilbo.  He pulls off burdens with Sam, moves to Buckleberry Ferry, but I play Nelya and exert him twice to get my sites 2 and 3 out (Weatherhills & Ford).  Now the Hobbits must fight (Buckleberry Ferry cancels skirmish phases, its a built-in stealth card).  I also play a Breath and Tip.  Merry (w/hobbit sword) battles, gets tipped and breathed on, and he stops.  I play Legolas and Aragorn w/bow and with my Strengths of Spirit I easily pick off his Uruks at site 4 and 5.  He moves into site 3 and faces Cantea (destroys weapons) and Ostea (makes himself fierce).  Luckily he played 2 Bounders but I play Fear to discard a Bounder and kill Pippin, Sam and Merry.  Where are his stealth cards??  I move into site 6 and stop, he just moves and I play Ostea, who overwhlems Frodo on the fierce skirmish (Bounder protects Frodo for the 1st skirmish).  Win +3 (3).<br>
<br>
Best: Getting a nice draw at site 3 with Strengths of Spirits.<br>
Worst: He didn&#39;t even play 8 stealth cards he just played 4.  Not the way to make a Hobbit deck.  And farmers??<br>
<br>
Game 2 v Stacey&#39;s Hobbits (R-frodo & 3 C-hobbits)<br>
Hobbits again?  Well, Stacey bids 0 so I go 1st.  He uses the Uruk and Moria archers.  Plus Bitter hatreds to kill Elves.  Ouch.  Unfortunately for him, I don&#39;t draw an elf all game.  Anyways, I pull Sam 1st turn and remove my burdens.  I play Aragorn and Bow and Sting (thats when i see the archers and 3 Bitter hatreds!), move to Buckleberry Ferry (again).  He plays an Orthanc Assassin Which Aragorn exerts thrice to kill, move to site 3 and he has nothing to play.  He plays some allies (no Farmers at least) and moves, but stops because he knows I play Nazgul and I will have a lot of pool at site 3 to use.  I move to site 4, armed with Strengths of Spirits in hand.  A Goblin Archer greets me at site 4, I take the archery damage and kill the goblin in skirmish, move to site 5 where Lurtz and an Assassin are waiting, but 3 Strength of Spirits, 1 exertion by Aragorn, and 2 PATHS kill the both of them.  He moves to site 3, I have nothing I can play, he stops there.<br>
<br>
I move to site 6, he plays 2 Goblin Marksmen, I take archery damage and kill them with Gandalf and Aragorn in skirmish.  I move again, and Lurtz and an Assassin again come to play, but Ranger&#39;s Verstatility and Archery damage  and a PATH kills them.  He moves to site 4, and stops.  I move to site 8, but he plays the site that adds +1 to archery for each minion archer, so he can&#39;t stop me, because he actually got 5 orcs out.  But I had fully healed with all the Athelas I had just played, so Aragorn picked off the 2 Marksmen (leaving 2 Runners and a Moria SCout, which were killed by Frodo w/Sting, Gandalf, and Aragorn).  I move to site 9, but I have no burdens so he draws no cards and only has an Orthanc Assassin to throw out, so I win the game.  Win +3 (6).<br>
<br>
Best: Not much, it wasn&#39;t a challenging game for me.<br>
Worst: Stacey only plays 3 stealth cards (why wouldn&#39;t you play with 8?).  He used those funky Hobbit events like Appetites and Stout and Sturdy.  I tried to explain how good stealth cards were.<br>
<br>
Game 3 v Franklin&#39;s archery/Sauron (Arwen & R-Legolas)<br>
Franklin won the last tourney I went to in Santa Rosa, so he was on like an 11-0 tourney run, no one could beat him. This was my 1st time playing him.  He bids 2, I go 1st, get Sam and pull off my burdens.  I get Sleep in my opening draw (I only have 1), so I have to hang on to it all game.  I get to site 3, then he plays Orc Bowmen and an Orc Assassin, Frodo or Sam must battle, so Frodo takes a wound.  Franklin plays Galadriel, Celeborn, the Mirror, Aragorn, bow, and Elven bow on Arwen.  Wow.  So every turn he uses his mirror, taking out 2 Nazgul and I never get anything going against him.  None of my minionshimmer the table.  All game he double moves me.  Darn mirror.  But I went first, so I&#39;ll get back to my fellowship.<br>
<br>
At site 3, I play Boromir, Legolas, and Aragorn.  I could Sleep away his Bowmen, but I decide to wait until more conditions are out.  I move to site 4, he plays a few trackers and a couple Under the Watching Eyes.  I kill the trackers no problem, and move to site 5, where he plays 2 Band of the Eyes on me, Gandalf and Aragorn each take a wound.  Then on his turn I have no Nazgul, so he uses the mirror to discard my Sleep.  Nuts, I should&#39;ve thought of that, that was dumb of me not to use Sleep when I had the chance.  Like I said, he double moves all game, so we&#39;re both at site 5.  I move to 6, face some orcs, but I&#39;m hurting.  He plays a couple Orcs and Hates away Boromir (exhausted from the Watching Eyes).  I kill his trackers again, and move to site 7 (Silverlode banks).  Ranger&#39;s Verstatility ensures no more Hates and I kill his Morgul Hunter and Band of the Eye with archery.  He moves to 7 easily, and I have to get to site 9 this turn, and luck is with me because at site 8 he can only play 3 orcs, not 5 to force me to stop.  I lose everyone except Arwen and Aragorn and frodo, of course, and I have 3 PATHS in hand, so I move to site 9 with no fear, losing everyone but Frodo to Archery (only 2 orc bowmen out) and killing all 6 of his orcs with 2 PATHS (all were trackers).  Win +3 (9).<br>
<br>
Best: PATHS all came up at the end, when I needed them.<br>
Worst: The mirror was bad enough, but most of my Nazgul were at the bottom of my deck, just bad luck on my part, combined with the Mirror I think you can see why I couldn&#39;t touch his fellowship.<br>
<br>
Game 4 v Chris Dejong&#39;s archery/Moria/Nazgul (R-Aragorn)<br>
Chris whupped me at my last tourney in Santa Rosa, so I was looking for retribution.  He bids 0, I go 1st, get Sam to pull off the burdens.  I play Albert Dreary & move to his Weatherhills, he plays They Are Coming (which I discard with Albert) and a Scavenger, which wounds Gandalf.  I move to the Ford, he has nothing else to play.  BTW, his deck is 110 cards.  He plays Legolas & Ranger&#39;s Sword, moves, I play Cantea & Breath.  He directs 2 archery to Cantea (so I can&#39;t destroy Aragorn&#39;s sword), Aragorn takes a wound & Breath then he has Frodo skirmish and plays PATH to kill Cantea.  He knows I play All Blades Perish so I&#39;m suprised he did that without Bounder out there.  So he moves again, I play Attea and a Tip, then Relentless Charge to kill Legolas.  Aragorn takes 2 wounds and is Tipped, so he is dead next turn.  I just move to the Mithril Mine and stop, hoping I can kill his Frodo.  He has no companions in hand, and I have Ostea to play for 4 to overwhelm Frodo at site 4.  Win +3 (12).<br>
<br>
Best: Quick wins are Nazgul&#39;s specialty.<br>
Worst: Not drawing my companions (not that I needed them).<br>
<br>
Game 5 v Ray Liu&#39;s Uruk/Nazgul (Arwen & R-Legolas)<br>
Ray is 3-1 (I&#39;m 4-0), so whoever wins this may well win the tourney, but there is another player at 3-1 too.  I loaned Ray 2 Savagery to Match Their Numbers since I never play Uruk myself, so he now had 4 Savageries in the deck.  Ouch, considering my game plan is to usually have 5-6 companions on table.  He bids 0, I play Sam to pull off my burdens and play Peter Jackson, uh...I mean Albert Dreary, then move to his Weatherhills.  He plays Lurtz, killing Sam and forcing me to stop.  He plays Sam and moves, I play Cantea, he exerts Legolas twice to wound Cantea twice, then Arwen battles and plays Defiance, but I have All Blades perish, so we skirmish a second time but another Defiance comes out.  Cantea dies, he moves to my Ford, but I have enough for Enquea for 1 and Ostea for 4 (make himself fierce), then I play relentless Charge to kill Legolas.  So Sam dies to Enquea, Arwen skirmishes Ostea, taking a wound, then skirmishes again, but Frodo dies to Enquea.  Very fast game, just like its supposed to be.  Win +3 (15).<br>
<br>
Best: Winning at site 3 in 5 minutes is something impressive I think.<br>
Worst: Beating Ray, since we&#39;re in the same squad.<br>
<br>
So I end up 1st place at 5-0, no one else is even 4-1, there is a 6-way tie for 2nd of people at 3-2.  Opposition totals place Stacey and Ray at a tie even for that, so they decide to have a final confrontation for 2nd place.  Ray wins easy (see my game vs Stacey above if you don&#39;t remember Stacey&#39;s deck).  Ray and I were joking about being the losers car before the tourney (we normally get beat down), but this time we are the winners car.  I win a deluxe starter, Ray gets a normal starter.  I also get to pick from the store&#39;s rare binder, so I choose Arwen, Ray chooses the cave Troll.  We both pull junk in our starters though, so it all balances out I guess.  Thanks for reading, I hope one of the teams won the Superbowl today.<br>
<br>
Props to:<br>
Ray for 2nd place, he doesn&#39;t have a lot of cards (thats why I loaned him some).<br>
Ron for being a good TD and running it nicely.<br>
Ed the store owner for letting us pick from the binder.<br>
Everyone I met at Epic Worlds, they&#39;re all cool people, just some of them need help with decks.<br>
Everyone who read this, and liked it.<br>
The winner of the Superbowl.<br>
Franklin, who did the right thing and lost to his elder, I found out he&#39;s only 15 (he looks older), 6 years younger than me, I told him he should respect his elders and he did, since he says he &quot;let&quot; me beat him (yeah, right).<br>
<br>
Slops to:<br>
The weird Hobbit decks I faced in the first 2 games, I told them how they should fix those decks up, they needed work BADLY, but the guys who played the decks were nice guys, and we had good trades.<br>
<br>
Slops again to:<br>
Those bad, bad, BAD hobbit decks I faced, they were just bad (but the players were cool).  Hobbit farmers??  Come on!! <br></font></blockquote><BR><font class="bfont"> <A HREF='/lotr/treports/treports.php?id=3327&view=1'>Read the Reviews</a><font class="bfont"> | <A HREF='/lotr/treports/treports.php'>Back to List</A></font><p><font class="bfont"> <b>You must be a member to contribute to Decktech.</b>  <p>Please <a href='/lotr/main/join.php'> become a registered member</a></font></font></td><td background="/lotr/gfx/mom/whi_09.gif"></td></tr>
